One of the best ways to learn more about Emacs is to get to know other people who use and customize Emacs. Here are a few resources for doing so.

* [[CategoryHomepage|Homepage]] -- home pages of Emacs friends, including '''you!'''
* EmacsForums -- web forums about Emacs all over the world
* EmacsMailingLists -- often also available as newsgroups
* EmacsNewsgroups -- beginner-focused, general, and technical discussions
* EmacsStackExchange -- post your technical questions
* InternetRelayChat -- often a good way to get real-time help
* PlanetEmacsen -- an aggregator of Emacs-related blogs
* [[Usergroups|Usergroups]] -- Emacs usergroups and meetups all over the world.
* [https://plus.google.com/108840863190686221561/ Google+: Emacs conferences and hangouts]
* [https://plus.google.com/communities/114815898697665598016 Google+: Emacs community]
